						               													<description>Narcopolis is an immersive and competitive Board Game. The Game is play in the South of United States during the years 2000.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The Goal? Become the new boss of the town. To become the new Boss, you have to be the one with the higher rate of reputation at the end of the Game. The Game finish either when someone arrive to 20 points of reputation or after 10 turns.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;There are 3 types of winning reputation:&amp;#10;1/ Doing some Jobs (missions)&amp;#10;2/ Play some influence Cards (Fight Club, Mob, Hired a Hitman&amp;hellip;) &amp;#10;3/ Finance electoral campaign&amp;#10;&amp;#10;To do that you have to earn money. There are 3 types of Winning it:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;1/ Develope Business&amp;#10;2/ Play some influence Cards (Fight Club, Mob, Hired a Hitman&amp;hellip;) &amp;#10;3/ The Humiliation (Sales reputation&amp;rsquo;s points)&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Each turn every player have to play 2 obligatory actions (take money and move) and can do 5 more actions (play or buy influence card, do or exchange job, develope new Business, conquer a new area by fighting or just Build up new Business, Buy or sale reputation point).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;To take territories to an enemy you have to play a dice fight which include a bluffing part. Even when you are unlucky you can be victorious.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Every table turn the first player revel a new event card which change, during a tour, a norm of the game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;It's a tactic Game with bluff and you have to be diplomatic and play dirty. Players light on the interactions and the fun around the table.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;-description from writer&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
